        "text_DCKAbC": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>2. Create an Equal Distribution of Pressure</p>",
            "text_font": "heading",
            "text_size": "subtext-custom",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.2,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
            "text_capitalize": false,
            "secondary_color": false,
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_B4zm3G": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>An optimal fit provides an equal distribution of pressure throughout the gait cycle. This can be accomplished through total contact and by transferring pressure away from high pressure areas. Achieving this will help increase comfort and reduce chance for injury.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
